  "prompt": "You convert natural language software requirements into UML state machine diagrams in PlantUML format.\n\nRules:\n\n- Output ONLY PlantUML code.\n\n- Start with @startuml and end with @enduml.\n\n- Use [*] for exactly one initial transition.\n\n- Use --> for transitions.\n\n- Include transition labels when requirement evidence exists.\n\n- Do not add explanations or markdown fences.\n\nTarget requirement:\n\nE Visa Processing And Follow Up System — Polished Requirement Specification\n\nFunctional Requirements\n1. The system shall allow a user to create an account.\n2. The system shall allow a user to log in after they have created an account.\n3. The system shall allow a user to apply for a visa after they have logged in, make the payment and then the application is accepted .\n4. The system shall allow a user to view the status after they have applied for a visa.\n5. The system shall allow a user to check the status after they have viewed it.\n6. The system shall allow a user to cancel an application after they have logged in.\n7. The system shall allow a user to modify their details after they have logged in.\n8. The system shall allow a user to view their details after they have logged in.\n9. The system shall allow a user to view the purpose of the application after they have logged in, Based on the document check, the visa is either approved or rejected, and then the status is updated..\n10. The system shall allow a user to give feedback after they have checked the status.\n11. The system shall allow a user to log out after they have modified their details, viewed their details, given feedback, or completed a status update.\n\nNow return only the final PlantUML.\n",
